<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <meta name="description" content="DNS Pilot support for Windows DNS benchmarking and guided setup.">
  <link rel="canonical" href="{{SITE_URL}}/">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
  <title>DNS Pilot Windows Support</title>
</head>
<body>
  <main>
    <header>
      <p class="eyebrow">DNS Pilot for Windows</p>
      <h1>Support</h1>
      <p>DNS benchmarking, saved profiles, and guided Windows DNS setup.</p>
    </header>
    <section><h2>Common Help</h2><ul>
      <li>Results estimate the current network path. They do not promise full browser, game, or internet speed improvement.</li>
      <li>The Store build never silently changes Windows DNS. Guided Apply copies DNS servers and opens Windows Settings.</li>
      <li>Quick Check is DNS-only. DNS + TCP adds connection-path estimates.</li>
      <li>Gaming presets are DNS + TCP estimates, not ICMP ping or in-match UDP latency.</li>
    </ul></section>
    <section><h2>Troubleshooting</h2><ul>
      <li>If candidates fail, check VPN, firewall, captive portal, MDM, corporate DNS policy, and IPv4/IPv6 reachability.</li>
      <li>After changing DNS manually, return to DNS Pilot and run Validate DNS.</li>
      <li>Custom domain targets accept hostnames only: omit protocol prefixes, paths, ports, and spaces.</li>
    </ul></section>
    <section><h2>Data</h2><p>DNS Pilot stores custom DNS profiles, domain suites, benchmark history, language, and preferences locally. The Store-safe build has no accounts, analytics, tracking, or cloud sync.</p></section>
    <section><h2>Contact</h2><p><a href="mailto:{{SUPPORT_EMAIL}}">{{SUPPORT_EMAIL}}</a></p></section>
  </main>
  <footer><a href="privacy.html">Privacy Policy</a></footer>
</body>
</html>
